./code-execution/spec.md` | Code Execution (PicoD) | 179 |\n| `/.../idle-cleanup/spec.md` | Idle Cleanup (Agentd) | 69 |\n| `/.../cli-toolkit/spec.md` | CLI Toolkit | 197 |\n| `/.../python-sdk/spec.md` | Python SDK | 133 |\n| `/.../deployment/spec.md` | Deployment (Helm) | 96 |\n| `/.../ci-cd/spec.md` | CI/CD | -- |\n| `/.../integrations/spec.md` | Integrations (Dify, PCAP) | 191 |\n\n**Changes directory delta-spec.md files (23 total):**\n```\nchanges/AR-002/delta-spec.md   changes/AR-003/delta-spec.md   changes/AR-004/delta-spec.md\nchanges/AR-005/delta-spec.md   changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md   changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md\nchanges/AR-010/delta-spec.md   changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md   changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md\nchanges/AR-018/delta-spec.md   changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md   changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md\nchanges/AR-021/delta-spec.md   changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md   changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md\nchanges/AR-024/delta-spec.md   changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md   changes/AR-026/delta-spec.md\nchanges/AR-027/delta-spec.md   changes/AR-028/delta-spec.md   changes/AR-029/delta-spec.md\nchanges/AR-030/delta-spec.md\n```\n\nNote: AR-001, AR-008, AR-009, AR-012, AR-013, AR-014, AR-015, AR-016 do NOT have delta-spec.md files (they have only proposal.md, design.md, and/or tasks.md).\n\n---\n\n### 3. Manifests / Helm Chart Files\n\n**No actual manifests/ directory or Helm chart files exist in this working copy.** The glob searches for `**/manifests/**`, `**/charts/**`, `**/crds/**`, `**/*helm*`, `**/Chart.*`, `**/values*`, `**/*.yaml`, `**/*.yml`, `**/Makefile`, and `**/Dockerfile*` all returned zero results.\n\nHowever, the **deployment design document** (`/.../deployment/design.md`) extensively documents the Helm chart structure that *should* exist in the real repository:\n\n- **Chart path:** `manifests/charts/base/`\n- **Chart.yaml:** apiVersion v1, name `agentcube`, version 0.1.0, appVersion 1.0.0\n- **Template files:** `manifests/charts/base/templates/` including:\n  - `workloadmanager.yaml` (Deployment + Service)\n  - `agentcube-router.yaml` (Deployment + Service)\n  - `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n  - `rbac-router.yaml` (conditional Router RBAC)\n  - `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` (conditional)\n- **CRDs:** `manifests/charts/base/crds/` containing:\n  - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`\n  - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml`\n- **values.yaml keys:** `redis.addr`, `redis.password`, `router.*`, `workloadmanager.*`, `volcano.scheduler.*`\n- **Dockerfiles:** `docker/Dockerfile`, `docker/Dockerfile.router`, `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n\n**AR-030** (`changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md`) is titled \"Helm Chart Templates and Values -- Delta Spec\" but is a **stub/placeholder** -- only 20 lines with TODO comments:\n```markdown\n# AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values — Delta Spec\n## Context\n- **Module:** `manifests`\n- **Language:** YAML\n- **Size:** L\n- **Base specs:** <!-- TODO: reference base specs -->\n## Delta Requirements\n<!-- TODO: Add requirements in Given/When/Then format -->\n## File Changes\n<!-- TODO: List planned file changes -->\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. OpenSpec Format Examples\n\nThe project uses a consistent **OpenSpec / Spec-Driven Development (SDD)** format across all spec files. The pattern is:\n\n**Module-level spec.md format:**\n```markdown\n# <Module> Specification\n\n## Purpose\n<One-paragraph description>\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: <Requirement name>\nThe system SHALL <normative statement using SHALL/SHOULD/MAY>.\n\n#### Scenario: <Scenario name>\n- **GIVEN** <precondition>\n- **WHEN** <action>\n- **THEN** <expected outcome>\n```\n\n**Change-level file structure (in `changes/AR-NNN/`):**\n- `proposal.md` -- Purpose, scope, impact analysis, alternatives, acceptance criteria\n- `delta-spec.md` -- Given/When/Then requirements specific to this change\n- `design.md` -- Architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy\n- `tasks.md` -- Implementation tasks with dependency graphs and parallelization groups\n\n**Example from AR-005 (Sandbox Create Handler) -- one of the most complete:**\n- proposal.md: 139 lines\n- delta-spec.md: 436 lines (very detailed Given/When/Then scenarios)\n- design.md: 636 lines\n- tasks.md: present\n\n**Example from AR-001 (CRD AgentRuntime type definition) -- no delta-spec.md:**\n- proposal.md: 105 lines\n- design.md: 636 lines\n- tasks.md: present\n\n---\n\n### 5. Manifests Module Structure\n\nThe **manifests module does not exist as actual files** in this working copy. It is referenced in documentation but the `manifests/` directory is absent. The only reference is:\n\n- `deployment/spec.md` line 9: \"installing/upgrading the AgentCube stack with Helm from `manifests/charts/base`\"\n- `deployment/design.md` line 58: \"Template files (`manifests/charts/base/templates/`)\"\n- `changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md`: Module is listed as `manifests`, Language as `YAML`, Size as `L` -- but content is all TODOs\n\nThe Go code references these paths in Makefile targets:\n- `make gen-crd` outputs to `manifests/charts/base/crds`\n- `make e2e` runs `helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base`\n\n---\n\n### 6. Configuration Files, values.yaml Patterns, Helm Templates\n\n**No actual YAML configuration files exist** in this working tree. However, the deployment design (`/.../deployment/design.md`) documents the complete values.yaml schema:\n\n**Key values.yaml structure (from design.md):**\n```yaml\nredis:\n  addr: \"\"           # Required by user\n  password: \"\"       # Empty permitted\n\nrouter:\n  replicas: 1\n  image: {repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router, pullPolicy: IfNotPresent, tag: latest}\n  service: {type: ClusterIP, port: 8080, targetPort: 8080}\n  resources: {limits: {cpu: 500m, memory: 512Mi}, requests: {cpu: 100m, memory: 128Mi}}\n  config: {}\n  extraEnv: []\n  serviceAccountName: \"\"\n  rbac: {create: false}\n\nworkloadmanager:\n  replicas: 1\n  image: {repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager, pullPolicy: IfNotPresent, tag: latest}\n  service: {type: ClusterIP, port: 8080}\n  resources: {limits: {cpu: 500m, memory: 512Mi}, requests: {cpu: 100m, memory: 128Mi}}\n  extraEnv: []\n\nvolcano:\n  scheduler: {enabled: false, replicas: 1, image: {repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler, ...}}\n```\n\n**CRD API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n**CRD Kinds:** `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter`\n\n**Example AgentRuntime YAML (from AR-001 design.md):**\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: python-sandbox\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  targetPort:\n    - name: web\n      port: 8080\n      protocol: HTTP\n      pathPrefix: /\n  podTemplate:\n    labels:\n      app: python-agent\n    spec:\n      containers:\n        - name: sandbox\n          image: python:3.11-slim\n          ports:\n            - containerPort: 8080\n          resources:\n            requests: {cpu: \"100m\", memory: \"128Mi\"}\n            limits: {cpu: \"1\", memory: \"512Mi\"}\n  sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n  maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. Go Package Structure (`pkg/`)\n\n| Package | Files | Purpose |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/` | (subdirs) | CRD type definitions for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter |\n| `pkg/apis/agents/` | (subdirs) | Agent-related API types |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/` | const.go, handler/, middleware/, reconciler/, response/ | Workload Manager HTTP API, handlers, auth middleware, sandbox reconciler |\n| `pkg/router/` | 16 .go files | HTTP router, session manager, JWT, proxy, load balancer, health, informers |\n| `pkg/store/` | 9 .go files | Session store interface + Redis + Valkey implementations |\n| `pkg/picod/` | 13 .go files + files/ subdir | PicoD daemon: auth, execute, files, server, sanitize |\n| `pkg/agentd/` | const.go, reconciler.go, reconciler_test.go | Idle cleanup controller reconciler |\n| `pkg/common/types/` | (subdir) | Shared type definitions |\n\n---\n\n### 8. Changes Directory (AR-001 through AR-030)\n\nEach AR (Action Request) directory contains a subset of: `proposal.md`, `delta-spec.md`, `design.md`, `tasks.md`.\n\n**Complete inventory:**\n\n| AR | proposal | delta-spec | design | tasks | Topic (inferred) |\n|----|----------|------------|--------|-------|-------------------|\n| AR-001 | Yes | No | Yes | Yes | CRD AgentRuntime type definition |\n| AR-002 | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | CRD CodeInterpreter type definition |\n| AR-003 | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | (CRD related) |\n| AR-004 | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | HTTP service framework |\n| AR-005 | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | Sandbox create handler |\n| AR-006 | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | (Sandbox related) |\n| AR-007 | No | Yes | No | No | (Unknown) |\n| AR-008 | Yes | No | Yes | Yes | (Unknown) |\n| AR-009 | Yes | No | Yes | Yes | (Unknown) |\n| AR-010 | No | Yes | No | No | (Unknown) |\n| AR-011 | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | (Unknown) |\n| AR-012 | Yes | No | Yes | Yes | (Unknown) |\n| AR-013 | Yes | No | Yes | Yes | (Unknown) |\n| AR-014 | No | No | No | No | (Empty or minimal) |\n| AR-015 | Yes | No | Yes | Yes | (Unknown) |\n| AR-016 | Yes | No | Yes | Yes | (Unknown) |\n| AR-017 | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | (Unknown) |\n| AR-018 | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | (Unknown) |\n| AR-019 | No | Yes | No | No | (Unknown) |\n| AR-020 | No | Yes | No | No | (Unknown) |\n| AR-021 | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | (Unknown) |\n| AR-022 | No | Yes | No | No | (Unknown) |\n| AR-023 | No | No | No | Yes | CLI invoke/status commands |\n| AR-024 | No | Yes | No | No | (Unknown) |\n| AR-025 | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | (Unknown) |\n| AR-026 | Yes | Yes | Yes | Yes | (Unknown) |\n| AR-027 | No | Yes | No | No | SDK CodeInterpreterClient |\n| AR-028 | Yes | Yes | No | No | SDK AgentRuntimeClient |\n| AR-029 | No | Yes | No | No | SDK HTTP underlying client |\n| AR-030 | Yes | Yes | No | No | Helm Chart templates/values (stub) |\n\n---\n\n### 9. Key Findings Summary\n\n1. **No manifests/ directory exists** -- Helm charts, CRD YAMLs, Dockerfiles, and Makefiles are all absent from this working copy. They are only documented in `deployment/design.md` and `deployment/spec.md`.\n\n2. **AR-030 (Helm Chart)** is a stub with TODO placeholders -- the manifests module work has not been spec'd out in detail yet.\n\n3. **The OpenSpec format is well-established** with a consistent Given/When/Then pattern using SHALL/SHOULD/MAY normative language.\n\n4. **The project is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform** for AI agents, with Go server components (WorkloadManager, Router, PicoD, Agentd) and Python client components (CLI, SDK).\n\n5. **The Go module** is `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` using Go 1.25.0 with dependencies on Gin, go-redis, controller-runtime, and K8s client-go.\n\n6. **CRD API group** is `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` with two CRDs: `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter`.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_285e88ffbffesHUcCp9lDoHhrH","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775869849600,"end":1775870168888}}}}
